<div class="wrap-narrow" id="release">
  <span class="eyebrow">Press Release</span>
  <div class="pr-wrap">
    <div class="pr-meta">
      FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE — EMBARGOED UNTIL JUNE 18, 2026<br>
      MEDIA CONTACT: Ayo Adepoju, We Plug Good Music &nbsp;·&nbsp; ayodele@wepluggoodmusic.com
    </div>
    <h2 class="pr-headline">Anie Delgado Reclaims Her Autonomy on Electric New Single "LOVERGRLL," Out June 18</h2>
    <p class="pr-subhead">The Cuban-American pop artist delivers her boldest statement yet — a pulsing dance-pop anthem about desire, limits, and refusing to be someone else's fantasy</p>
    <div class="pr-body">
      <p>Miami-born, Los Angeles-based singer-songwriter Anie Delgado announces her new single "LOVERGRLL," out June 18, 2026. The track marks a pivotal creative turn for the Cuban-American artist — rawer, more defiant, and more sonically charged than anything she has released to date.</p>
      <p>Produced with a buzzing, euphoric urgency, "LOVERGRLL" is energetic dance-pop with a dual personality: driving synths and a fierce, cutting verse delivery pull against an ethereal, almost hypnotic vocal hook. The result is a song that feels simultaneously euphoric and confrontational — an irresistible tension that mirrors the story at its heart.</p>
      <div class="pr-pullquote">
        "This song is about being a recovering people pleaser — someone who gives so much warmth that others mistake it for an open invitation. I'm done apologizing for having limits."<br><br>
        — Anie Delgado
      </div>
      <p>The song was born from a real experience: after reaching out to a producer she deeply admired with entirely professional intentions, Delgado was met with hostility when she declined his advances. That moment crystallized something she had been living with for years — the way women's friendliness is routinely sexualized, and the exhausting labor of managing other people's projections while simply trying to exist and connect.</p>
      <p>Lyrically, "LOVERGRLL" is seductive and unapologetic. Delgado inhabits the character she is accused of being — magnetic, intoxicating, inescapable — but entirely on her own terms. It is, in her own words, the "messier, more chaotic, cuntier version" of Taylor Swift's "Mirror Ball" — quiet reflection replaced with something electric and uncompromising.</p>
      <p>Anie Delgado has built her following through a body of work defined by social clarity and emotional intelligence. Her single "Dancing While the World is on Fire" raised funds for climate non-profit Zero Hour and earned a placement in <em>Billboard</em>. "Galaxy" accumulated over 100,000 streams; "Stranger from the Internet" was licensed to CBS's <em>The Young and the Restless</em>. A new EP is in development.</p>
      <p>"LOVERGRLL" is available everywhere on June 18, 2026. Press assets, high-resolution photography, and a private preview link are available upon request.</p>
    </div>
