      <h2 class="section-title">Anie Delgado</h2>
      <p>Anie Delgado is a Cuban-American artist and bilingual Alternative-Pop songwriter from Miami, Florida. Steeped in Cuban heritage through dominoes, late-night dancing, and the reverberating beats of the Florida Keys, Anie has a musical imprint that goes all the way back to her first guitar in fourth grade.</p>
      <p>Throughout adolescence, writing songs became a way of documenting her life — inspired by Lorde, Taylor Swift, and Madonna. In 2018, she relocated to Los Angeles to pursue her full-time career as an artist.</p>
      <p>Her single "Dancing While the World is on Fire" raised funds for climate non-profit Zero Hour and was featured in <em>Billboard</em>. Working with producers PJ Bianco (Fifth Harmony, Jonas Brothers) and Nicke Lee (Lil Nas X, Ariana Grande), Anie released "Galaxy" with over 100,000 streams, and earned a sync placement on CBS's <em>The Young and the Restless</em> with "Stranger from the Internet."</p>
      <p>"99¢ Jesus" contends with removing those who don't value you — a thematic reversal of the male gaze. With an EP in development, Anie Delgado is a new female pop artist to watch.</p>
